channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Earthquake rocks Los Angeles
item.description: A 4.4 magnitude earthquake rocked the Los Angeles region early Monday afternoon.

item.title: Patreon will have to use Apple's in-app purchase system or be removed from the App Store
Harris ahead of Trump in Michigan, Wisconsin and Pennsylvania, new poll says
item.description: A new poll by The New York Times and Siena College shows Vice President Kamala Harris ahead of former President Donald Trump in several battleground states ahead of the November election. CBS News campaign reporter Aaron Navarro has more.

item.title: Crews begin demolishing Texas church where gunman killed more than two dozen in 2017
item.description: Crews have started to tear down a Texas church where a gunman killed more than two dozen worshippers in 2017

item.title: Google and Selena Gomez partner to fund teen mental health in the classroom
8/12: CBS News 24/7 Episode 2
item.description: Elon Musk set to interview Donald Trump; Car fire spreads to brush in California

item.title: Trump wants a role in setting interest rates. Some economists say it's a bad idea
item.description: Donald Trump recently said the president should have a role in setting interest rates but some economists say that's a bad idea.

item.title: Judge says Maine can forbid discrimination by religious schools that take state tuition money
New study estimates 47,000 heat-related deaths in Europe last year
item.description: Researchers say this is the second-highest heat related mortality burden in the last decade, following 2022 when an estimated 60,000 people in Europe died due to heat.

item.title: Blink Fitness, an affordable gym operator, files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy
item.description: Gym operator Blink Fitness has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection

item.title: Graham Thorpe died after being hit by train as family confirm he took own life
Trump X interview with Elon Musk expected as Iran hack claims surface
item.description: Former President Donald Trump will chat with Elon Musk on X Monday as his campaign claims it has been hacked by Iran. CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi reports. Meanwhile, Vice President Kamala Harris' campaign is preparing for an appearance with President Biden, the first campaign event he will attend with Harris since he announced he was dropping out of the race. CBS News senior White House correspondent Weijia Jiang has more.

item.title: House explosion killed 2 people, caused 'millions' in damage: Authorities
item.description: Two people were found dead after an explosion Sunday morning leveled a home and rocked a suburban Baltimore neighborhood, authorities said.

item.title: Hubble View Of Runaway Black Hole Leaves Massive Streak Of Stars In Its Wake
Demolition begins at Sunderland Springs church site of 2017 mass shooting
item.description: Until now, First Baptist Church of Sutherland Springs had been kept as a memorial that included the names of the people killed.
